21. Advanced SQL (Interview Focus)
Pivot
SELECT *
FROM sales
PIVOT
(
SUM(amount)
FOR year IN ([2024],[2025])
) p;
Unpivot
Recursive CTE
Dynamic SQL
MERGE Statement
MERGE target t
USING source s
ON t.id=s.id
WHEN MATCHED THEN
UPDATE SET t.name=s.name
WHEN NOT MATCHED THEN
INSERT(id,name)
VALUES(s.id,s.name);
SQL Learning Roadmap (30 Days)
Week	Topics
Week 1	SELECT, WHERE, ORDER BY, GROUP BY, HAVING
Week 2	Joins, Subqueries, Set Operators
Week 3	CTEs, Window Functions, CASE, Date Functions
Week 4	Views, Procedures, Functions, Indexes, Performance Tuning
Top 10 Interview Topics (Learn First)
Joins
Group By & Having
Aggregate Functions
Window Functions
CTEs
Subqueries
CASE Statements
Date Functions
Set Operators
Indexes

For a Data Engineer (Azure/Fabric/Spark/Databricks) role, spend 40% of your SQL practice on Joins, Window Functions, CTEs, Aggregations, and Query Optimization, because these topics appear most frequently in real projects and interviews.
